lead_paragraph: Cori Chambers scored 21 points and Ashley Houts made four free throws in the final 30 seconds as the No. 8-ranked Georgia women’s team held off No. 11 Stanford, 74-69, in Athens, Ga. Stanford (2-3) lost both games of its weekend trip to the Southeastern Conference, falling to No. 4 Tennessee, 77-60, on Friday.
